# Task 3 — Secure Coding Review

## Overview
Security audit of a Python Flask web application to identify
and fix common vulnerabilities using static analysis and
manual code review.

## Tools Used
- Bandit (Static Analysis)
- Manual Inspection
- OWASP Top 10

## Vulnerabilities Found
- SQL Injection (4 locations)
- OS Command Injection
- Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
- Weak Hashing (MD5)
- Hardcoded Credentials
- Missing Authentication
- Unrestricted File Upload
- Path Traversal
- And more...

## Results
| Severity | Before | After |
|----------|--------|-------|
| HIGH     |   3    |   0   |
| MEDIUM   |   6    |   0   |
| LOW      |   3    |   3   |

## How to Run
pip install flask bandit bcrypt python-dotenv
bandit -r vulnerable_app/app_vulnerable.py

